      "text": "SYSTEM DESIGN: WEB CRAWLER FOR SEARCH ENGINE\n\nFUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n- Domain policy management: domains, priority (1 per domain), trust, seeds, run seeds\n- Schedule/dispatch crawl work by priority & trust with capacity throttling\n- Crawl HTML + JS, respect robots.txt, emit artifacts (text, outlinks, canonical URL, status, timing, content hash, robots decision)\n- Deduplicate outlinks within no-rescan window\n- Feed search engine with content, metadata, link graph signals, diagnostics\n\nNON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n- Scale: ≤1,000 VMs, single region/cloud, 100k seeds/day, 100M fetches/day, avg HTML 100KB, text 10KB,\n  10k fetches/sec global peak across distinct target hosts (per-host limited by politeness)\n- Latency: connect/read 2s, max 5 retries, 1s backoff, 25s hard attempt deadline\n- Availability: control plane 99.9%, execution 99.99%, indexing handoff 99.999%\n- Freshness: max SLA (P1 48h, P2 2w, P3 3m, P4 1y); min no-rescan window (P1 2h, P2 1d, P3 1w, P4 1m)\n- Retention: raw HTML 3d, extracted text 1y, diagnostics 2w\n- Cost/backpressure: stay within VM quota; delay dispatch when saturated; shed lowest-priority URLs first; no storage caps v1\n\nASSUMPTIONS\n- Public web only; HTML + JS rendering; single region; broad coverage; robots.txt only\n\nINVARIANTS\n- No-ReCrawl-Within-Window: a canonical URL may start a new attempt only after its no-rescan window; attempt starts at lease acquisition\n- Single-Lease Retries: all retries occur within one lease\n- Max Crawl Time: 25s wall-clock per attempt\n- VM Budget Enforcement: total compute ≤1,000 VMs; delay new leases when saturated\n- Politeness: max 1 concurrent fetch per target host (original + final) with ≥1s delay\n- Domain-Priority Uniqueness: each domain maps to exactly one priority\n- At-Least-Once Fetch, Exactly-Once Index: retries allowed; index idempotent on (canonical_url, content_version)\n\nARCHITECTURE & APIS\n\nCONTROL PLANE\n- DomainPolicy Service (authoritative DB):\n  PolicyClass, TrustClass, Seeds, Domains (domain_id, eTLD+1); exposes materialized policy to Frontier\n\nDATA PLANE\n- Seeding Ingestion: stateless adapter; reads DomainPolicy, writes to Frontier\n- Frontier (authoritative DB, key=canonical_url): dedupe, no-rescan windows, eligibility, admission & shedding; consults policy cache\n- Dispatch: stateless; trust affects weighting only; dedupe key remains canonical_url\n  Message: {canonical_url, target_host, priority_id, trust_id, work_item_id, crawl_budget_ms}\n- Lease Service (authoritative locks, DB key=lease_id):\n  POST /leases:acquire {work_item_id, canonical_url, worker_id} → {lease_id, attempt_id, deadline}\n  POST /leases/{lease_id}:complete | abort\n- Crawlers: execute fetch; emit results\n  Result: {attempt_id, lease_id, canonical_url, original_url, final_url, fetch_time, http_status, content_hash, raw_html_ref, outlinks[]}\n- Indexing Pipeline (search-owned): content-version store (canonical_url, content_hash), link graph DB, diagnostics stack; idempotent indexing",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "SYSTEM DESIGN: WEB CRAWLER FOR SEARCH ENGINE\n\nFUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n- Domain policy management: domains, priority (1 per domain), trust, seeds, run seeds\n- Schedule/dispatch crawl work by priority & trust with capacity throttling\n- Crawl HTML + JS, respect robots.txt, emit artifacts (text, outlinks, canonical URL, status, timing, content hash, robots decision)\n- Deduplicate outlinks within no-rescan window\n- Feed search engine with content, metadata, link graph signals, diagnostics\n\nNON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS\n- Scale: ≤1,000 VMs, single region/cloud, 100k seeds/day, 100M fetches/day, avg HTML 100KB, text 10KB,\n  10k fetches/sec global peak across distinct target hosts (per-host limited by politeness)\n- Latency: connect/read 2s, max 5 retries, 1s backoff, 25s hard attempt deadline\n- Availability: control plane 99.9%, execution 99.99%, indexing handoff 99.999%\n- Freshness: max SLA (P1 48h, P2 2w, P3 3m, P4 1y); min no-rescan window (P1 2h, P2 1d, P3 1w, P4 1m)\n- Retention: raw HTML 3d, extracted text 1y, diagnostics 2w\n- Cost/backpressure: stay within VM quota; delay dispatch when saturated; shed lowest-priority URLs first; no storage caps v1\n\nASSUMPTIONS\n- Public web only; HTML + JS rendering; single region; broad coverage; robots.txt only\n\nINVARIANTS\n- No-ReCrawl-Within-Window: a canonical URL may start a new attempt only after its no-rescan window; attempt starts at lease acquisition\n- Single-Lease Retries: all retries occur within one lease\n- Max Crawl Time: 25s wall-clock per attempt\n- VM Budget Enforcement: total compute ≤1,000 VMs; delay new leases when saturated\n- Politeness: max 1 concurrent fetch per target host (original + final) with ≥1s delay\n- Domain-Priority Uniqueness: each domain maps to exactly one priority\n- At-Least-Once Fetch, Exactly-Once Index: retries allowed; index idempotent on (canonical_url, content_version)\n\nARCHITECTURE & APIS\n\nCONTROL PLANE\n- DomainPolicy Service (authoritative DB):\n  PolicyClass, TrustClass, Seeds, Domains (domain_id, eTLD+1); exposes materialized policy to Frontier\n\nDATA PLANE\n- Seeding Ingestion: stateless adapter; reads DomainPolicy, writes to Frontier\n- Frontier (authoritative DB, key=canonical_url): dedupe, no-rescan windows, eligibility, admission & shedding; consults policy cache\n- Dispatch: stateless; trust affects weighting only; dedupe key remains canonical_url\n  Message: {canonical_url, target_host, priority_id, trust_id, work_item_id, crawl_budget_ms}\n- Lease Service (authoritative locks, DB key=lease_id):\n  POST /leases:acquire {work_item_id, canonical_url, worker_id} → {lease_id, attempt_id, deadline}\n  POST /leases/{lease_id}:complete | abort\n- Crawlers: execute fetch; emit results\n  Result: {attempt_id, lease_id, canonical_url, original_url, final_url, fetch_time, http_status, content_hash, raw_html_ref, outlinks[]}\n- Indexing Pipeline (search-owned): content-version store (canonical_url, content_hash), link graph DB, diagnostics stack; idempotent indexing",
